      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "`gemm_add()` had an invalid dispatch path for the out is C case. When callers reused C storage as the output, the wrapper marked the operation as in-place but still called `gemm_add_out()` with `C=None`. That violates the `gemm_add_out` custom-op contract, which requires `C: Tensor`, and can trigger PyTorch schema/assert failures.\r\n\r\nThis change fixes the wrapper to dispatch that case to `gemm_add_inplace()` instead. The normal out-of-place path still goes through `gemm_add_out()`.\r\n\r\nA regression test was added to cover `gemm_add(A, B, C, out=C, alpha=tensor, beta=1.0)` so the wrapper contract stays correct.",
    "created_at": "2026-04-08T16:42:37Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-13T04:16:14Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-13T04:16:14Z",
    "merged_at": "2026-04-13T04:16:14Z",
